my:Hazard.my:ControlMeasures:
a) Working areas must be clear of hazardous materials and items that can cause potential harm; 
b) When conducting jobs that pose a risk to the seafarer, the appropriate risk assessment must be consulted prior to work commencing;
c) All working spaces must have adequate illumination; 
d) Consideration must be given to weather conditions when working outside e.g., water on deck, pitching / rolling moments; 
e) Equipment, not in use, should be stowed appropriately to avoid interference with operations.

a) Consult specific task risk assessment; 
b) At all times the prescribed instruments / tools must be in use; 
c) Use of appropriate PPE through out every operation; 
d) Damaged equipment should be removed and not used; 
e) If correct equipment is not available then the task cannot be undertaken.

a) Operation must be carefully planned and all crew briefed before starting; 
b) All equipment thoroughly checked prior to use; 
c) Adequate number of crew available; 
d) Take into account the inexperience of a young person; 
e) Young persons must at all times be supervised by an experienced member of crew.

a) Crew made aware of any physical and / or mental risks associated with the job in hand; 
b) Crew instructed how to safely operate all equipment intended for use; 
c) Person in charge to monitor physical and mental health of young person at regular intervals; 
d) More frequent breaks to be considered.
